works.description: For anyone who likes two-wheeled choppers, Harley Davidson holds a very special place. Three years ago, the company decided to let people into its museum, to let them go through the elaborate history that the bike maker has had since its inception in 1903. This year, the latest collection on show would be the “Collection X: Weird, Wild Wonders of the Harley Davidson Museum,” which will showcase out-of-the-box ideas including an all-leather replica of a Harley Davidson chopper, the parts of which are known to be functional. This show will also focus on various memorabilia such as T-shirts, belt buckles, brake light helmets
